    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ancient Persian gold coins possibly introduced by Darius I in the late 6th century BCE and in use until the early 4th century BCE.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000012271/Doty, Macmillan Encyclopedic Dictionary of Numismatics (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Antiguas monedas persas de oro, posiblemente introducidas por Darío I en el siglo VI a.C. tardío y en uso hasta el siglo IV a.C. temprano.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Oude Perzische gouden munten, mogelijk in circulatie gebracht door Darius l aan het eind van de 6e eeuw v.C. en gebruikt tot aan het begin van de 4e eeuw v.C.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
